-- Catalonia’s Finance Chief Demands Higher Payments for Medicines
-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 2012-05-03T07:33:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-03/catalonia-s-finance-chief-demands-higher-payments-for-medicines.html
People earning more than 100,000 euros
($131,430) a year should pay the whole cost of medication,
Andreu Mas-Colell, the finance chief of  Spain ’s Catalonia
region, said in an article published by  El Pais  today.  He also said hospital patients should pay five euros for
each day they are in care, to cut the public deficit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
